# UI Responsiveness & Visual Consistency

Before writing or modifying ANY UI code, ensure full mobile responsiveness and visual consistency across all screen sizes. Follow these rules strictly.

## Layout & Structure
- Use flexbox or CSS Grid for all layouts — never fixed widths in px for containers
- All containers must use: `width: 100%`, `max-width`, and horizontal padding (`px-4` minimum)
- Stack elements vertically on mobile (`flex-col`), side by side on desktop (`sm:flex-row` or `md:flex-row`)
- Never let content overflow horizontally — test mentally at 375px width (iPhone SE)

## Spacing & Symmetry
- Use consistent spacing scale (Tailwind: 2, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16) — never arbitrary values
- Padding and margins must be symmetric: if left has `p-4`, right has `p-4`
- Gap between elements must be uniform within the same section
- Sections must have equal vertical breathing room (`py-8 md:py-16`)

## Typography
- Font sizes must scale: `text-sm` on mobile → `text-base` on desktop
- Never use fixed font sizes that break on small screens
- Line height and letter spacing must remain readable at all sizes
- Headings: `text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl` (always responsive)

## Components
- Buttons: full width on mobile (`w-full`), auto width on desktop (`sm:w-auto`)
- Cards: full width on mobile, grid layout on desktop (`grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`)
- Forms: stack labels and inputs vertically; use `space-y-4` for consistent gaps
- Images: always `max-w-full h-auto` to prevent overflow

## Breakpoints (Tailwind)
- `sm`: 640px
- `md`: 768px
- `lg`: 1024px
- `xl`: 1280px

Test at: 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1024px+ (desktop).
